comments.body:
> I've installed it from buster-backports, the one that mentioned in the official instructions [here](https://podman.io/getting-started/installation).
> Looks like the current version which can be obtained from [here](https://github.com/rootless-containers/rootlesskit/releases) will work for now. Any chance that someone would fix the package please?

@hetzbh did it specifically pull in from buster-backports? The buster-backports repo was only meant for libseccomp dependency. There's a new slirp4netns available in the Kubic project repo itself, https://build.opensuse.org/package/show/devel:kubic:libcontainers:stable/slirp4netns . I will enforce that as the minimum dependency for podman, but that fix will show up on the Kubic Stable only once we have 3.0.0 released, until then I will push changes only to the Kubic Testing project.
